Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%g}(chopped into 2cm chunks, no need to peel) and pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the potatoes roast, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the garlic, lemon zest, @olive oil for the marinade{1%tbsp} and half the @dried oregano{1%tsp} into a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together.

Add the @British chicken breasts{2} to the marinade and mix well until evenly coated.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lay the marinated chicken onto another baking tray. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything roasts, cut the @medium tomato{1}(cut into 1cm pieces). Cut the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g}(cut into 1cm cubes). Halve the @olives{30}(halved).

Squeeze the lemon juice into a #large bowl{}. Add the @Dijon mustard{10%g}, remaining oregano, @sugar for the dressing{1%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together until well combined. Stir the tomato to the dressing, then set aside until serving.

When everything is ready, cut each chicken breast widthways into 5 slices.

Add the @baby leaf mix{50%g}, roasted potatoes, Greek style salad cheese and olives to the tomato bowl. Toss everything together to dress it, then share the salad between your #bowls{}.

Lay the sliced chicken on top and tuck in. Enjoy!